changes.description:
Upgrade the BTB to use 2-bit saturating counters.
1. Declare `logic [1:0] btb_bht[0:63];`.
2. Declare `logic btb_pred_taken;`.
3. Change the combinational read block to:
   ```systemverilog
   assign btb_idx = pc[7:2];
   assign btb_hit = btb_valid[btb_idx] && (btb_tag[btb_idx] == pc);
   assign btb_pred_taken = btb_hit && btb_bht[btb_idx][1];

   always_comb begin
     next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target : (btb_pred_taken ? btb_target[btb_idx] : pc + 32'd4);
   end
   ```
4. Declare update logic wires before the `always_ff` block:
   ```systemverilog
   logic [5:0] update_idx;
   logic       update_is_hit;

   assign update_idx = btb_update_pc[7:2];
   assign update_is_hit = btb_valid[update_idx] && (btb_tag[update_idx] == btb_update_pc);
   ```
5. In the `always_ff` block, replace the entire `if (btb_update)` section with:
   ```systemverilog
   if (btb_update) begin
     if (update_is_hit) begin
       if (btb_update_valid) begin
         if (btb_bht[update_idx] != 2'b11) btb_bht[update_idx] <= btb_bht[update_idx] + 2'd1;
         btb_target[update_idx] <= btb_update_target;
       end else begin
         if (btb_bht[update_idx] != 2'b00) btb_bht[update_idx] <= btb_bht[update_idx] - 2'd1;
       end
     end else if (btb_update_valid) begin
       btb_valid[update_idx] <= 1'b1;
       btb_tag[update_idx] <= btb_update_pc;
       btb_target[update_idx] <= btb_update_target;
       btb_bht[update_idx] <= 2'b10;
     end
   end
   ```
6. Keep the reset logic exactly as it is (it clears `btb_valid` loop).

